"The outlook for global equities, interest rates and exchange rate markets has become uncertain", analysts at Deutsche Bank wrote in a note to investors.
"We believe that raw materials will not be able to escape the contagion.
From a raw materials perspective our most pressing concern is to what extent the American virus will spread globally and specifically to China".
