Actress Heather Locklear arrested for driving under the influence of drugs.
Actress Heather Locklear, the Amanda of the popular series Melrose Place, was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara, California, for driving under the influence of drugs.
A witness saw her performing risky maneuvers as she tried to drive her car out of the parking lot in Montecito, according to a spokesman for the California Highway Patrol who told People magazine.
The witness specified that at about 4:30 p.m. the Locklear "was slamming the accelerator, making a lot of noise, and trying to get the car out of the parking lot with sudden back and forth maneuvers.
Shortly after, the witness, who apparently did not recognize the actress at first glance, saw Locklear pull over to a nearby road and exit the vehicle.
It was this person who alerted the emergency services, because "she was worried about Locklear's life".
When the police patrol arrived, they found the actress sitting inside her vehicle, which was partially blocking the road.
"She seemed confused", and so the officers took her to a drug and alcohol treatment center for testing.
According to a police spokesman, the actress was cooperative and the alcohol overdose hypothesis was dismissed from the start, although "according to what was observed by officers at the outset, we believe Locklear was under the influence of some drug".
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of an unspecified substance and was booked into the local jail around 7 p.m., only to be released a few hours later.
