Llamazares urges the Andalusian Federation of the UI to take responsibility in the Silva case
The general coordinator of the UI and member of the Izquierda Unida party, Gaspar Llamazares, confirmed today that it will be up to the regional federation of training to make a decision on the case of the former youth and sports advisor of the Municipality of Seville, Francisco Manuel Silva, who resigned last week following the accusation of clientelism.
