There is also a lack of establishments offering training, advice and assistance to small and medium-sized enterprises, which could open up business opportunities.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for video writing as opposed to Word; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for emulating Powerpoint presentations; Dbase, as in the case of the most famous Access is the program that allows you to work on databases; Draw, is finally the graphic module.
